title: Did Putin's dambusters 'deliberately destroy' the Nova Kakhovka dam in retaliation over Kherson?
description: Satellite images have emerged showing damage to the Russian-held Nova Kakhovka dam near Kherson as Putin's troops left a trail of destruction in their retreat from the city.

title: Pentagon drags out decision after probe into woke diversity chief accused of anti-white people tweet
description: An investigation was begun in September into Kelisa Wing, the chief diversity, equity and inclusion officer in the Pentagon's Education Activity office. The review has taken almost 2 months

title: Why Latvia offers the best deal on the Christmas market: Riga tops list for best bargain break
description: If you're hoping to visit a Christmas market this year, then you may want to try further east. For Latvia (pictured) is the best value for money for a winter shopping trip, the Post Office has found.

title: Sydney stockbroker's $130 million estate pits his shoe designer ex-wife against his son
description: Donna-May Bolinger, 62, is in an NSW Supreme Court fight with Ned Bell, the adult son of her late ex-husband, high-profile stockbroker Colin Bell.

title: Biden touches down in Cambodia where he will huddle with allies amid North Korea threat
description: North Korea's provocative missile launches are providing a backdrop to President Joe Biden's meeting with key allies Japan and South Korea at a summit in Cambodia.

title: Iran's most senior diplomat in Britain summoned by James Cleverly over 'threats' made to journalists
description: Foreign Secretary James Cleverly said he had called in Iran's charge d'affaires, Mehdi Hosseini Matin, to make it clear that 'intimidation of any kind' would not be tolerated.

title: Argos launches its first half-Christmas tree for space-strapped Britons this festive season
description: The annual nightmare of trying to squeeze a Christmas tree, presents and all your extra relatives into one room could soon be over.

title: Yale sophomore student, 20, reveals she hid her attempted suicide from college after she was raped
description: A Yale University student (not pictured) has told how she was forced to drop out of her course after she attempted suicide in June 2021. She has since returned, but said they did not sufficiently help her.

title: Prince Andrew was 'promised by lawyers the fallout from his sex abuse lawsuit would 'all blow over''

title: Medibank hack: Australia plans to 'hack the hackers' as government begins new policing push
description: Australia has sent a pointed message to Russian cyber criminals believed to be behind the Medibank data theft saying it will 'hack the hackers'.

title: Ministers, police and prosecutors warned they have created a 'permissive culture' of fraud
description: Successive governments have failed to tackle the 'scourge' of what has become the country's most common crime, with more than 40 million UK adults targeted by swindlers in the first half of this year.

title: Kwasi Kwarteng 'rewriting history on Budget turmoil' after claims he warned Liz Truss about tax cuts
description: Allies of Liz Truss accused Kwasi Kwarteng of 'rewriting history' yesterday, after he claimed he warned her she was moving too far and too fast with her radical economic reforms.

title: Schools 'heading for bankruptcy' by spring 2024 without a drastic cuts, business leaders warn

title: Are YOU being hit by inflation hardest? Map shows where cost of living is hitting hardest

title: Chris Davidson convicted of child sex offence as surfer's dark past emerges after death

title: Nadine Dorries says she went out on dates so she could eat while working as a trainee nurse

title: Weather forecast this weekend in Australia: Storms expected in NSW and Victoria, flood warnings

title: Thousands of nurses could strike for MONTHS as union has £50 million to pay them during walkouts
description: The Royal College of Nursing (RCN) topped up its strikes fund by £15 million ahead of balloting its more than 300,000 members, according to the union's latest accounts.

title: Michael Slater: Former Australian cricketer turns attention to becoming a mental health counsellor

title: Mum blasts school for serving her daughter a 'basically empty' ham baguette

title: PAUL BRACCHI: This couple claimed £84,000 a year in benefits, but barely spent a penny on children
description: PAUL BRACCHI: Gemma Brogan and her partner Christopher Bennett claimed £84,000 a year in benefits but spent barely a penny on the children found in squalor at their Eastbourne home.

title: Cong Tran said LEGO obsessed son Chandler diagnosed with osteosarcoma cancer on his leg
description: Chandler Tran, 8, was enjoying his Easter holidays when his parents noticed he began to limp, spotting a lump no larger than a pea on his shin, which turned out to be a rare form of disease.
